The paper deals with a problem in computational geometry, specifically in the area of visibility queries in polygonal domains. This suggests that cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also presents a new data structure for answering these queries, which falls under the area of data structures and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another likely sub-category. The use of algorithms to solve the problem also suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) may be a relevant sub-category. Additionally, the problem has applications in robotics (cs.RO) and spatial information systems (cs.SI), making these sub-categories also possible.
